SIMPLE: distasteful
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Distasteful
<hw>Dis*taste"ful</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Unpleasant or disgusting to the taste; nauseous;
loathsome.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Offensive; displeasing to the feelings;
disagreeable; <as>as, a <ex>distasteful</ex> truth</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Distasteful</qex> answer, and sometimes unfriendly
actions.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Manifesting distaste or dislike; repulsive.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Distasteful</xex> looks.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Nauseous; unsavory; unpalatable; offensive;
displeasing; dissatisfactory; disgusting.</syn></p>

<p>- <wordforms><wf>Dis*taste"ful*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Dis*taste"ful*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Distasteive</ent>⟦br⟧
